Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Workflow Runner (Backend Engineer)* position with *Profound*. I bring over three years of professional experience in high-performance backend systems, distributed architectures, and agentic workflows, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across multiple engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend systems that directly reflect *the architectural rigor required to build the foundational agentic layer and high-performance workflow execution engines*. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected a concurrent multi-agent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph, implementing DAG workflow primitives that enable reliable, scalable tool execution across a distributed surface. I also developed a foundational agentic interaction layer in Rust and TypeScript that translates natural-language intents into idempotent, validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints—requiring the same focus on reliability and schema consistency that the Workflow Runner demands. To ensure operational excellence, I implemented backpressure and scheduling strategies that reduced end-to-end latency by 60%, maintaining system stability under high-concurrency loads. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed durable backend workflows using AWS Step Functions to orchestrate long-running job execution, ensuring reliable state management and idempotency. I also built a cloud-agnostic storage engine using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handled distributed file operations across AWS S3, GCS, and MinIO via streaming patterns—giving me direct experience with the relational data modeling and real-time state systems Profound utilizes. These roles have prepared me to *shape the core primitives, real-time control plane, and durable state systems that power Profound’s intelligent workflows* and drive impact within your fast-moving engineering team.

My technical projects and research have further deepened my expertise in systems design and real-time streaming—skills that translate directly into *the systems thinking, speed, and iteration that Profound values in its builders*. I built Dark Factory, a distributed execution orchestrator in Rust that manages real-time event-driven loops via PTY and implements a streaming signaling layer using Y-crdt to coordinate agentic loops across machines. This project required solving the exact challenges of reliable job orchestration, state synchronization, and real-time delivery that are central to the Workflow Runner. Additionally, as an AI Researcher at Pace University, I engineered high-performance training pipelines and optimized model inference using vLLM for scalable serving, ensuring minimal latency for production AI applications. Beyond building these systems, I led workshops on systems programming and agentic workflows for 50+ developers, demonstrating *the technical leadership and clear communication required to ship reliable systems at scale*. This experience has shaped me into a builder who prioritizes rigor, durability, and execution, all of which I would bring to *Profound and its mission to build the foundational agentic layer for modern companies*.

I have always been passionate about *building durable solutions for AI visibility and empowering companies to control their AI presence* and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of *the mission of helping brands navigate the shift to Answer Engines*. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

